It may be observed that, upon the principles of Aristotle and Porphyry, a generic property can only be regarded as a property with respect to the highest species of which it is predicable. As regards all subordinate species, it must be considered as an accident. Mobile, for example, a property of corpus, is an accident to animal, and to homo, as not convertible with them.
